                            Summary on Grant Application Form</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailValue" style="padding:5px;">
                        <span id="lblAbstract">The design and construction of an instrument is proposed which provides a novel method - positron dosimetry - for the measurement of doses of implanted ions, with significant advantages over other available techniques.  The non-destructive method, applied using a compact apparatus of novel design, is especially suited to measurements within 100nm of the surface, which will be particularly relevant to the next generation of smaller scale semiconductor devices.</span>
                        </td>
		</tr>
